{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772562286,"nonce":"27/BnYOOPk73Hr8c+jtaYylREHI=","title":"Uneven spacing between CDE template cards in ComponentLibrary","message":"Visual gap between cards 1 and 2 in the CDE Controllers section appears ~3x larger than between cards 2 and 3, even though the code uses uniform `space-y-2` (8px) between all CDE template cards.\n\n## What is observed\n\nIn the ComponentLibrary sidebar, the CDE Controllers section renders `CdeTemplateCard` components with `space-y-2` (8px) on the container. The gap between card 1 (CDE Standard) and card 2 (CDE + Decay) appears visually much larger (~20â€“24px) than the gap between card 2 and card 3 (CDE + Anti-NF), which appears to be the expected ~8px.\n\n## Relevant code\n\n- `web/src/components/panels/ComponentLibrary.tsx`: `CdeTemplateCard` rendered in `\u003cdiv className=\"space-y-2\"\u003e` â€” no conditional or first-child-specific overrides\n- `web/tailwind.config.js`: `shadow-soft: \"0 12px 32px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08)\"` â€” 12px Y-offset + 32px blur â†’ shadow visually extends up to 44px below each card, well past the 8px gap\n- `CdeTemplateCard` className includes `hover:-translate-y-0.5` which shifts the hovered card up 2px (layout-independent), creating asymmetric visual spacing if a card is hovered when observed\n\n## Leading theories (code inspection only, not DevTools-confirmed)\n\n1. **Shadow bleed**: The large `shadow-soft` (12px Y-offset, 32px blur) means each card casts a shadow far below its bottom edge, into the next card and beyond. The first inter-card gap may appear heavier/larger due to the background gradient (body: `radial-gradient(circle at top left, #fefefe 0%, #f4f5f7 40%, #eef1f6 100%)`) showing through the sidebar's `bg-white/90`, making shadow contrast vary by vertical position.\n\n2. **Hover asymmetry**: If card 2 is hovered when the gap is observed, `hover:-translate-y-0.5` shifts it up 2px visually (not in layout), making the gap above card 2 appear ~10px and below ~6px. Combined with `shadow-soft` â†’ `hover:shadow` transition (much smaller shadow on hover), the asymmetry is amplified.\n\n## What to check in DevTools\n\n- Computed `margin-top` on each `.space-y-2` child button to confirm they are all exactly 8px\n- Actual rendered height of each card (should all be ~76px with 2-line descriptions)\n- Whether card 1 description wraps to 1 line vs 2 lines at the current sidebar width (1-line card would be ~60px, not ~76px)\n\n## Possible fixes\n\n- Reduce `shadow-soft` Y-offset and blur: e.g., `0 2px 8px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08)` (note: used in canvas nodes too â€” check visual impact there)\n- Remove or reduce `hover:-translate-y-0.5` on `CdeTemplateCard`\n- Increase `space-y-2` to `space-y-3` so the actual gap is more forgiving of shadow bleed","files":null}]}